WHAT FOLDER SHOULD YOU DOWNLOAD THE DRIVER

* Make sure that you have python installed in your computer - https://www.python.org/downloads/

-- How to run tests in windows PowerShell --
1. navigate to the project folder
2. Create a virtual environment. Type > "python -m venv env"
3. Activate the virtual environment:
    a. Go to the scripts folder. Type > "cd ProjectFolder/env/Scripts"
    b. Activate the virtual environment. Type >  ".\activate"
4. Install the requirements:
    a. Navigate project root folder
    b. Type > "pip install -r requirements.txt"
5. Run the tests using pytest:
    a. Go back to the project root folder
    b. Type > "python -m pytest ."
